<% set_meta_tags og: {
  title: "Blog: About Our Name",
	description: "<description>"
} %>

<% set_meta_tags twitter: {
  card: "All the latest Leksi news, announcements, posts, and more!",
  title: "Blog: About Our Name",
  description: "<description>"
} %>
<nav class="breadcrumb mb-5">
  <%= link_to "Home",
              root_path,
              class: "breadcrumb-item",
              alt: "Go to the Home page",
              title: "Go to the Home page"
  %>
  <%= link_to "Blog",
              blog_path,
              class: "breadcrumb-item",
              alt: "Go to the main Blog page",
              title: "Go to the main Blog page"
  %>
  <span class="breadcrumb-item active">
    About Our Name
  </span>
</nav>
<div id="blog-body">
	<div class="blog-header">
		<div class="container">
			<h1 class="blog-title">The Leksi Blog</h1>
			<p class="lead blog-description">
				Catch up and connect with us over all things Leksi related - latest news,
				announcements, posts, and more.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-8 blog-main">
				<div class="blog-post">
					<h2 class="blog-post-title">
            <div class="float-left pr-3">
              <%= image_tag "blog/emoji_thinking.png",
                            class: "img-fluid img-thumbnail",
                            width: 150,
                            height: 150,
                            alt: "Thinking Emoji",
                            title: "Thinking Emoji"
              %>
            </div>
						About Our Name
					</h2>
					<p class="blog-post-meta">June 19, 2017</p>
          <div class="clear mb-3"></div>
					<p>
            So from where exactly does our name <em>Leksi</em> come?
            As with many things in life, sometimes the answer to our question
            is right in front of us. Take a look at the image
            below; see anything familiar?
					</p>
          <p>
            <%= image_tag "blog/leksi-about-our-name.png",
                          class: "img-fluid img-thumbnail",
                          alt: "Leksi Blog: About Our Name",
                          title: "Leksi Blog: About Our Name"
            %>
          </p>
          <p>
            .
            <br>
            .
            <br>
            .
            <br>
            .
            <br>
            .
            <br>
            .
            <br>
            .
            <br>
            .
            <br>
            .
          </p>
          <p>
            SPOILER ALERT: If you haven't figured it out yet, look at the
            pronunciation of the word above, which is "lexicon". What are its
            first five letters?
          </p>
          <p>
            Yep, it's <em>leksi</em>! We wanted a name that is short
            and catchy, but more importantly relates to vocabulary. What
            do you think?
          </p>
          <%= render "blog/post_footer" %>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="col-sm-3 offset-sm-1 blog-sidebar">
				<div class="sidebar-module sidebar-module-inset">
					<h4>About</h4>
					<p>
						We believe students should be able to
						<em>define their future</em>. With our online Leksi app, students
						will be able to become stronger readers and writers by completing
						evidenced-based vocabulary activities that are highly engaging.
				</div>
				<div class="sidebar-module">
					<h4>Say Hello</h4>
					<ol class="list-unstyled">
						<li>
							<%= link_to "Facebook",
														"https://www.facebook.com/LeksiEducation",
														target: "_blank",
														title: "Connect with the Leksi page on Facebook!",
														alt: "Connect with the Leksi page on Facebook!"
							%>
						</li>
						<li>
							<%= link_to "Twitter", "https://twitter.com/LeksiEducation",
													target: "_blank",
													title: "Send Leksi a tweet!",
													alt: "Send Leksi a tweet!"
							%>
						</li>
					</ol>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
